  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Typically, it involves three key stages: placement (introducing illegal funds into the financial system), layering (concealing the source through complex transactions), and integration (making funds seem legitimate). Specific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but most anti-money laundering laws criminalize intentionally disguising the origins of money obtained through criminal activity.",
